cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use geistlib in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "geistlib: a dependency-free inference engine for small LLMs"
abstract: >-
  geistlib is a high-performance, dependency-free inference engine that runs
  small LLMs (Gemma 4, ternary BitNet b1.58) as a single static binary — no
  BLAS, Python, or CUDA — CPU-first with experimental Metal/Vulkan GPU
  backends, tuned for edge hardware such as the Raspberry Pi 5.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Schlegel
    given-names: Germar
    affiliation: "geisten Holding UG (haftungsbeschränkt)"
repository-code: "https://github.com/geisten/geistlib"
url: "https://github.com/geisten/geistlib"
version: "0.5.0"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - llm
  - inference
  - cpu
  - edge
  - quantization
  - bitnet
  - on-device-agent
